ICYMI: Another Hoax Gone Wild: Former FBI Agent Pleads Guilty to Tampering With Evidence 

A former FBI agent who was involved in an investigation of former Missouri Gov. Eric Greitens in 2018 pleaded guilty to misdemeanor tampering with evidence in the case on March 23, a day before jury selection was set to start in his trial on seven felony counts, including perjury.

"What everyone recognizes now is what we said from the beginning, is that this was a criminal witch hunt against me," Greitens said.

The investigation was looking into whether Greitens snapped a picture of a woman at his house in 2015. The alleged picture has never been found.

Gendron, filmed wearing a military uniform, has been taken into custody by the Buffalo Police Department. He has been described as 'heavily-armed.' 

Eric County District Attorney John Flynn says the shooter could be charged with multiple counts of first-degree murder as early as Saturday night.
